    tool_output=ToolOutput(
        output='# Definition and Reconciliation of Segment Adjusted EBITDA\n\n## Definition\n\n**Segment Adjusted EBITDA** is defined as **segment income (loss) from operations** excluding:\n\n1. Depreciation and amortization\n2. Share-based compensation\n3. Restructuring charges\n4. Impairment\n\nIt is a **non-GAAP measure** whose most directly comparable GAAP measure is **segment income (loss) from operations**.\n\n> *"Segment Adjusted EBITDA is defined as segment income (loss) from operations excluding (i) depreciation and amortization, (ii) share-based compensation, (iii) restructuring charges, and (iv) impairment."*\n\n---\n\n## Role as a Performance Measure\n\n> *"Adjusted EBITDA and Segment Adjusted EBITDA are key performance measures that our management uses to assess our financial performance as well as for internal planning and forecasting purposes. We consider Adjusted EBITDA and Segment Adjusted EBITDA to be meaningful performance measures for investors to evaluate our operating performance and to compare the financial results."*\n\nManagement cautions that other companies may calculate these measures differently, so they **should not be considered in isolation** or as a substitute for GAAP measures and should be read alongside reconciliations to GAAP.\n\n---\n\n## Reconciliation Tables by Segment\n\n### Three Months Ended March 31, 2026\n\n| (in millions) | Space | Connectivity | AI | **Total Reportable Segments** |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Income (loss) from operations | $(662) | $1,188 | $(2,469) | **$(1,943)** |\n| Depreciation and amortization | 166 | 783 | 1,493 | **2,442** |\n| Share-based compensation | 145 | 116 | 378 | **639** |\n| Restructuring charges | — | — | (11) | **(11)** |\n| **Segment Adjusted EBITDA** | **$(351)** | **$2,087** | **$(609)** | **$1,127** |\n\n### Three Months Ended March 31, 2025\n\n| (in millions) | Space | Connectivity | AI | **Total Reportable Segments** |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Income (loss) from operations | $(70) | $1,033 | $(936) | **$27** |\n| Depreciation and amortization | 162 | 510 | 771 | **1,443** |\n| Share-based compensation | 108 | 75 | 49 | **232** |\n| Restructuring charges | — | — | 4 | **4** |\n| Impairment | 24 | — | — | **24** |\n| **Segment Adjusted EBITDA** | **$224** | **$1,618** | **$(112)** | **$1,730** |\n\n### Year Ended December 31, 2025\n\n| (in millions) | Space | Connectivity | AI | **Total Reportable Segments** |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Income (loss) from operations | $(657) | $4,423 | $(6,355) | **$(2,589)** |\n| Depreciation and amortization | 757 | 2,376 | 3,568 | **6,701** |\n| Share-based compensation | 515 | 369 | 1,063 | **1,947** |\n| Restructuring charges | — | — | 487 | **487** |\n| Impairment | 38 | — | — | **38** |\n| **Segment Adjusted EBITDA** | **$653** | **$7,168** | **$(1,237)** | **$6,584** |\n\n### Year Ended December 31, 2024\n\n| (in millions) | Space | Connectivity | AI | **Total Reportable Segments** |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Income (loss) from operations | $21 | $2,006 | $(1,561) | **$466** |\n| Depreciation and amortization | 637 | 1,508 | 1,679 | **3,824** |\n| Share-based compensation | 472 | 296 | 16 | **784** |\n| Restructuring charges | — | — | 213 | **213** |\n| Impairment | 24 | 39 | — | **63** |\n| **Segment Adjusted EBITDA** | **$1,154** | **$3,849** | **$347** | **$5,350** |\n\n### Year Ended December 31, 2023\n\n| (in millions) | Space | Connectivity | AI | **Total Reportable Segments** |\n|---|---|---|---|---|\n| Income (loss) from operations | $(1) | $469 | $(3,973) | **$(3,505)** |\n| Depreciation and amortization | 571 | 884 | 1,180 | **2,635** |\n| Share-based compensation | 427 | 249 | 3 | **679** |\n| Restructuring charges | — | — | 237 | **237** |\n| Impairment | — | — | 3,775 | **3,775** |\n| **Segment Adjusted EBITDA** | **$997** | **$1,602** | **$1,222** | **$3,821** |\n\n---\n\n## How It Is Calculated — Summary\n\nFor each segment, the calculation follows this formula:\n\n> **Segment Adjusted EBITDA = Segment Income (Loss) from Operations + Depreciation & Amortization + Share-Based Compensation + Restructuring Charges + Impairment**\n\n### Segment-by-Segment Highlights\n\n**Space Segment:**\n- Generated positive Segment Adjusted EBITDA in most periods, declining from $997M (2023) → $1,154M (2024) → $653M (2025) → $(351)M (Q1 2026).\n- Declines driven by accelerated investment in Starship development and launch facilities, partially offset by NASA CRS missions and a U.S. Department of War contract.\n\n**Connectivity Segment (Starlink):**\n- The primary earnings engine, growing from $1,602M (2023) → $3,849M (2024) → $7,168M (2025) → $2,087M (Q1 2026).\n- Growth driven by subscriber expansion, enterprise adoption, and supply chain efficiencies reducing user terminal production costs.\n\n**AI Segment (xAI):**\n- Transitions from positive EBITDA of $1,222M (2023) → $347M (2024) → to negative EBITDA of $(1,237)M (2025) → $(609)M (Q1 2026).\n- The reversal reflects a strategic pivot to rapidly scaling compute infrastructure (cloud computing, GPU costs, data centers). Management expects a **multi-year investment horizon** before sustained positive Segment Adjusted EBITDA.\n\n### Notable Adjustments Driving the Difference Between GAAP and Non-GAAP\n\n| Adjustment | Impact |\n|---|---|\n| **Depreciation & amortization** | Consistently the largest add-back (e.g., $6,701M in 2025 total), reflecting heavy capital investment in satellites, launch vehicles, and data centers. |\n| **Share-based compensation** | Growing substantially (e.g., $1,947M in 2025), especially in the AI segment ($1,063M in 2025). |\n| **Restructuring charges** | Concentrated in the AI segment (e.g., $487M in 2025). |\n| **Impairment** | Notably, a $3,775M impairment in the AI segment in 2023 (related to Twitter brand rebranding); minimal thereafter. |',
